  "prompt": "Would you say I am bisexual?",
  "response": "Sexuality is a deeply personal and individual experience, and only you can truly determine how you identify. Here are some questions to help you reflect:\n\n1. **Attraction to More Than One Gender**: Do you experience romantic, emotional, or sexual attraction to people of more than one gender? This is a common characteristic of bisexuality, but it can vary from person to person.\n\n2. **Fluidity and Exploration**: Have you found that your attractions feel fluid or open to different genders at different times? Bisexuality can encompass a wide range of experiences and isn\u2019t limited to equal attraction to all genders.\n\n3. **How You Feel About Labels**: Do you feel that the term \"bisexual\" resonates with you? Labels are tools to help describe your experience, but they aren\u2019t required if they don\u2019t feel right.\n\n4. **Self-Acceptance**: Are you comfortable exploring and embracing your feelings and attractions, regardless of labels?\n\nRemember, there\u2019s no rush to define yourself, and your understanding of your sexuality may evolve over time. If you\u2019re unsure, take your time to explore your feelings, seek support, or talk to people you trust. You\u2019re not alone in this journey!",
